.TH BlockDrop 6 "2026-03-22" "1.2" "Game Manual"
.SH NAME
BlockDrop \- a color\-matching falling blocks puzzle game
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B BlockDrop
.SH DESCRIPTION
Blockdrop is a terminal\-based puzzle game built using ncurses.
The game features falling blocks of various sizes and shapes that must be
cleared by matching colors with neighboring blocks on a 12x18 grid.
.PP
Unlike traditional falling blocks games, BlockDrop uses a unique color\-matching
mechanic: when a piece lands, any adjacent blocks of the same color (from
a different piece) are cleared using a flood\-fill algorithm (Not including corners).
This creates dynamic chain reactions as blocks fall to fill empty spaces.
.SH GAMEPLAY
The game is played on a 12x18 grid. Pieces fall from the top of the screen,
and the player must position and rotate them to create color matches.
.SS Piece Types
.TP
.B Linear 2
A horizontal or vertical line of 2 blocks.
.TP
.B Linear 3
A horizontal or vertical line of 3 blocks.
.TP
.B Square
A 2x2 square of 4 blocks.
.TP
.B L\-Shape
An L\-shaped piece made of 4 blocks.
.TP
.B T\-Shape
A T\-shaped piece made of 5 blocks.
.SS Colors
Pieces are randomly assigned one of five colors:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Red
.IP \(bu 2
Yellow
.IP \(bu 2
Light Blue
.IP \(bu 2
Pink
.IP \(bu 2
White
.RE
.SS Color Matching Mechanic
When a piece lands, the game checks each block of the newly\-placed piece.
If any neighboring blocks (above, below, left, or right) have the same color
but belong to a different piece, those blocks are marked for clearing. The
matching blocks blink briefly (0.5 seconds) before being removed from the grid.
.SS Chain Reactions
After blocks are cleared, individual block gravity is applied: each column
is scanned from bottom to top, and any floating blocks are pulled down. If a
falling block lands on a piece of the same color (but different ID), another
match is triggered. This can create satisfying chain reactions for bonus points!
.SH CONTROLS
.TP
.B Left Arrow
Move piece left
.TP
.B Right Arrow
Move piece right
.TP
.B Down Arrow
Move piece down faster
.TP
.B Up Arrow
(Restricted \- does nothing)
.TP
.B Space
Rotate piece clockwise 90 degrees
.TP
.B Enter
Start or pause the game
.TP
.B Esc
First press: pause and show exit warning
.br
Second press: exit the game
.SH SCORING
Players earn 25 points for each block cleared. When blocks clear and cause
a chain reaction, each block cleared in the chain also earns 10 points.
.PP
The game speed increases by 30% for every 500 points scored, making the
game progressively more challenging.
.SH HIGH SCORES
The highest score achieved is saved in a file called
.B .ntc_highscore
in the user's home directory. This file is created with mode 0600 (user\-readable
and writable only) to protect score data.
